  "body": "\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Sometimes the \"Offline\" gray message is still visible after device goes online. When airplane mode is turned off the indicator disappears for a second and appears again. Then, it won't go away until the app is killed and opened again. I could reproduce it 3/7 times.  \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe offline indicator should always hide when device goes online.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSometimes the offline indicator does not disappear after device goes online:\r\n\r\n![img_7527dfec1594-1 jpeg 2018-01-09 00-25-43](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/34697604-2345869a-f4d4-11e7-9d9c-983e7204934c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to Chats tab or a chat screen\r\n- Turn on airplane mode to go offline\r\n- Turn off airplane mode to go online\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12 (TestFlight)\r\n* Tested on: iPhone 6, iOS 11.2.1\r\n",
